(1)
East 233rd Street, adjoining the N.W. corner of Bronx Boulevard, showing the Bronx River Inn. It was built in 1885. The view is in a westerly direction.

June 6, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from the opposite direction (viewed eastward), and including a 2½-story house, No. 597, at the N.W. corner of Bronx Boulevard.

June 6, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

East 233rd Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of Bronx Boulevard. The 1-story brick building, at the corner, bears No. 4200 on the last named thoroughfare, while the two adjoining houses bear Nos. 611 and 613 East 233rd Street.

June 6, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
